Find.name: RoomType_Everyone_Desc
Find.value:
A standard room.
Standard rooms are displayed in the lobby for everyone to join.

Replace.name: RoomType_Everyone_Desc
Replace.value: Modded hosting in public lobbies is not recommended due to the potential for instability and unexpected behavior that can disrupt gameplay for all participants. Modifications may introduce bugs or conflicts that were not present in the original game, leading to crashes, unfair advantages, or a poor experience for players. Furthermore, joining a modded lobby without understanding the changes can lead to confusion and frustration, ultimately harming the community's enjoyment and trust. It's best to keep modded content in private sessions where all participants are aware of and agree to the modifications.

Find.name: RoomType_PassCodeOnly_Desc
Find.value:
This room only allows players who know the passcode to join. It will be listed in the lobby screen,
but requires a passcode to join.
Players that were invited will not require a passcode.

value.value:
A broken high-performance assault rifle.
Performance of the rifle is greatly reduced due to it having been repaired with spare parts.

Holding the trigger (pressing and holding the attack button) will continually fire shots.
Fired bullets are susceptible to air resistance and decrease in power depending on distance.

At the moment being fire, the bullet's power is the maximum of the spec (Damage value shown on the right). 
Its power will gradually decrease and become the minimum of the spec (Damage value shown on the right) when reaching its limit of the range.
